00:31:59,476 --> 00:32:01,535
<i>and I was getting yelled at.</i>

500
00:32:05,115 --> 00:32:07,709
Sit down if you want to.

501
00:32:07,784 --> 00:32:10,048
<i>I didn't know who I might meet</i>

502
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:11,553
<i>or what they might ask.</i>

503
00:32:11,621 --> 00:32:14,385
You ever been
on a real shrimp boat?

504
00:32:14,457 --> 00:32:16,220
No.

505
00:32:16,292 --> 00:32:19,056
But I been on a real big boat.

506
00:32:19,129 --> 00:32:22,064
I'm talking about
a shrimp catching boat.

507
00:32:22,132 --> 00:32:25,067
I been working on
shrimp boats all my life.

508
00:32:25,135 --> 00:32:27,399
I started out
on my uncle's boat

509
00:32:27,470 --> 00:32:29,404
when I was about maybe 9.

510
00:32:29,472 --> 00:32:32,407
I was just looking
into buying my own boat

511
00:32:32,475 --> 00:32:34,409
and got drafted.

512
00:32:34,477 --> 00:32:37,742
My given name
is Benjamin Buford Blue.

513
00:32:37,814 --> 00:32:40,078
People call me Bubba,

514
00:32:40,150 --> 00:32:42,584
just like one of them
old redneck boys.

515
00:32:42,652 --> 00:32:43,914
Can you believe that?

516
00:32:43,987 --> 00:32:46,080
My name's Forrest Gump.

517
00:32:46,156 --> 00:32:48,420
People call me Forrest Gump.

518
00:32:48,491 --> 00:32:51,426
<i>So Bubba was from
Bayou La Batre, Alabama,</i>

519
00:32:51,494 --> 00:32:53,223
<i>and his mama cooked shrimp.</i>

520
00:32:55,198 --> 00:32:57,564
<i>And her mama
before her cooked shrimp,</i>

521
00:32:57,634 --> 00:33:01,229
<i>and her mama before her mama
cooked shrimp, too.</i>

522
00:33:01,304 --> 00:33:03,067
<i>Bubba's family knew everything</i>

523
00:33:03,139 --> 00:33:05,573
<i>there was to know about
the shrimping business.</i>

524
00:33:05,642 --> 00:33:07,906
I know everything
there is to know

525
00:33:07,977 --> 00:33:09,239
about the shrimping business.

526
00:33:09,312 --> 00:33:11,746
I'm going into
the shrimping business for myself

527
00:33:11,815 --> 00:33:14,079
after I get out of the army.

528
00:33:16,986 --> 00:33:17,975
O.K.

529
00:33:18,054 --> 00:33:19,316
Gump!

530
00:33:19,389 --> 00:33:21,983
What's your sole purpose
in this army?

531
00:33:22,058 --> 00:33:24,492
To do whatever you tell me,
Drill Sergeant!

532
00:33:24,561 --> 00:33:28,156
God damn it, Gump,
you're a goddamn genius.

533
00:33:28,231 --> 00:33:30,665
That's the most outstanding
answer I've ever heard.

534
00:33:30,733 --> 00:33:33,327
You must have
a goddamn I.Q. Of 160.

535
00:33:33,403 --> 00:33:35,997
You are goddamn gifted,
Private Gump.

536
00:33:37,240 --> 00:33:39,504
Listen up, people!

537
00:33:39,576 --> 00:33:42,511
<i>Now for some reason,
I fit in the army</i>

538
00:33:42,579 --> 00:33:44,513
<i>like one of them round pegs.</i>

539
00:33:44,581 --> 00:33:45,843
<i>It's not really hard.</i>

540
00:33:45,915 --> 00:33:47,849
<i>You just make your bed neat,</i>

541
00:33:47,917 --> 00:33:49,350
<i>remember to stand up straight,</i>

542
00:33:49,419 --> 00:33:51,011
<i>and always answer every question</i>

543
00:33:51,087 --> 00:33:53,021
<i>with "Yes, Drill Sergeant."</i>

544
00:33:53,089 --> 00:33:54,522
Is that clear?

545
00:33:54,591 --> 00:33:56,855
Yes, Drill Sergeant!

546
00:33:56,926 --> 00:34:00,362
What you do is drag your nets
along the bottom.

547
00:34:00,430 --> 00:34:01,692
On a good day,

548
00:34:01,764 --> 00:34:04,699
you can catch over
a hundred pounds of shrimp.

549
00:34:04,767 --> 00:34:06,029
Everything goes all right,

550
00:34:06,102 --> 00:34:07,865
2 men shrimping 10 hours,

551
00:34:07,937 --> 00:34:10,030
less what you spends on gas...

552
00:34:10,106 --> 00:34:12,199
Done, Drill Sergeant!

553
00:34:12,275 --> 00:34:13,708
Gump!

554
00:34:15,278 --> 00:34:18,213
Why did you put that weapon
together so quickly?

555
00:34:18,281 --> 00:34:20,215
You told me to,
Drill Sergeant.

556
00:34:20,283 --> 00:34:21,875
Jesus H. Christ.

557
00:34:21,951 --> 00:34:23,885
This is a new company record.

558
00:34:23,953 --> 00:34:25,386
If it wasn't a waste

559
00:34:25,455 --> 00:34:26,888
of a fine enlisted man,

560
00:34:26,956 --> 00:34:29,390
I'd recommend you for O.C.S.,
Private Gump.

561
00:34:29,459 --> 00:34:31,723
You're going to be
a general someday!

562
00:34:31,794 --> 00:34:33,728
Now disassemble your weapon
and continue!

563
00:34:35,798 --> 00:34:37,732
Anyway, like I was saying,

564
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:40,064
shrimp is the fruit
of the sea.

565
00:34:40,136 --> 00:34:43,401
You can barbecue it,
boil it, broil it,

566
00:34:43,473 --> 00:34:44,906
bake it, sauté it.

567
00:34:44,974 --> 00:34:48,068
They's, uh, shrimp kabobs,
shrimp creole,

568
00:34:48,144 --> 00:34:52,080
shrimp gumbo,
pan fried, deep fried,

569
00:34:52,148 --> 00:34:53,410
stir fried.

570
00:34:53,483 --> 00:34:55,246
There's pineapple shrimp

571
00:34:55,318 --> 00:34:58,185
and lemon shrimp,
coconut shrimp,

572
00:34:58,254 --> 00:34:59,380
pepper shrimp,

573
00:34:59,455 --> 00:35:01,889
shrimp soup, shrimp stew,

574
00:35:01,958 --> 00:35:03,550
shrimp salad,

575
00:35:03,626 --> 00:35:05,389
shrimp in potatoes,

576
00:35:05,461 --> 00:35:06,894
shrimp burger,

577
00:35:06,963 --> 00:35:08,726
shrimp sandwich.

578
00:35:10,967 --> 00:35:13,060
That... That's about it.

579
00:35:17,307 --> 00:35:20,470
<i>Nighttime in the army
is a lonely time.</i>

580
00:35:20,543 --> 00:35:22,977
<i>We'd lay there in our bunks,</i>

581
00:35:23,046 --> 00:35:25,480
<i>and I'd miss my mama,</i>

582
00:35:25,548 --> 00:35:28,142
<i>and I'd miss Jenny.</i>

583
00:35:31,554 --> 00:35:33,488
Hey, Gump.

584
00:35:33,556 --> 00:35:36,150
Get a load of the tits on her.

585
00:35:48,905 --> 00:35:50,338
<i>Turns out...</i>

586
00:35:50,406 --> 00:35:52,499
<i>Jenny had gotten
into some trouble</i>

587
00:35:52,575 --> 00:35:55,840
<i>over some photos of her
in her college sweater.</i>

588
00:35:55,912 --> 00:35:58,107
<i>And she was
thrown out of school.</i>

589
00:35:58,181 --> 00:36:01,344
~ My baby does the hanky panky ~

590
00:36:01,417 --> 00:36:03,851
<i>But that wasn't a bad thing,</i>

591
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:06,354
<i>'cause a man who owns a theater</i>

592
00:36:06,422 --> 00:36:07,855
<i>in Memphis, Tennessee,</i>

593
00:36:07,924 --> 00:36:09,516
<i>saw those photos</i>

594
00:36:09,592 --> 00:36:13,358
<i>and offered Jenny
a job singing in a show.</i>

595
00:36:13,429 --> 00:36:15,522
<i>The first chance I got,</i>

596
00:36:15,598 --> 00:36:17,862
<i>I took the bus up to Memphis</i>

597
00:36:17,934 --> 00:36:20,198
<i>to see her perform in that show.</i>

598
00:36:20,269 --> 00:36:21,702
That was Amber, Amber Flame.

599
00:36:21,771 --> 00:36:23,204
Give her a big hand.

600
00:36:23,272 --> 00:36:26,207
And now, for your listening
and viewing pleasure,

601
00:36:26,275 --> 00:36:28,038
direct from Hollywood,
California,

602
00:36:28,111 --> 00:36:29,874
our very own beatnik beauty.

603
00:36:29,946 --> 00:36:32,210
Let's give a big round of applause

604
00:36:32,281 --> 00:36:34,044
to the luscious Bobbie Dylan.

605
00:36:43,292 --> 00:36:49,060
~ How many roads
must a man walk down ~

606
00:36:49,132 --> 00:36:54,502
~ Before you can
call him a man? ~

607
00:36:54,570 --> 00:37:00,770
~ Yes, and how many seas
must the white dove sail ~

608
00:37:00,843 --> 00:37:02,777
<i>Her dream had come true.</i>

609
00:37:02,845 --> 00:37:04,779
~ Before she sleeps
in the sand? ~

610
00:37:04,847 --> 00:37:06,678
<i>She was a folksinger.</i>

611
00:37:06,749 --> 00:37:09,843
~ Yes, and how many times ~

612
00:37:09,919 --> 00:37:12,979
~ Must the cannonballs fly ~

613
00:37:13,056 --> 00:37:17,652
~ Before they're
forever banned? ~

614
00:37:17,727 --> 00:37:19,058
Shake it up now.

615
00:37:19,128 --> 00:37:20,561
Somebody get her a harmonica.

616
00:37:20,630 --> 00:37:22,359
~ The answer, my friend ~

617
00:37:22,432 --> 00:37:24,195
~ Is blowin' in the wind ~

618
00:37:24,267 --> 00:37:25,700
<i>This ain't Captain Kangaroo.</i>

619
00:37:25,768 --> 00:37:28,532
Hey, honey, I got
something here for you.

620
00:37:28,604 --> 00:37:30,663
Hey! God damn it!

621
00:37:30,740 --> 00:37:33,004
Hey, you stupid jerk!

622
00:37:33,076 --> 00:37:34,839
I'm singing a song here.

623
00:37:37,914 --> 00:37:39,347
Polly, get out here!

624
00:37:39,415 --> 00:37:41,849
Shut up yourself!

625
00:37:41,918 --> 00:37:43,385
Just shut up!

626
00:37:45,955 --> 00:37:48,890
Forrest! What are you
doing here?

627
00:37:48,958 --> 00:37:50,289
What are you doing?

628
00:37:50,359 --> 00:37:51,291
- Hey!
- Aw!

629
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:53,123
What are you doing, Forrest?

630
00:37:53,196 --> 00:37:55,221
Let me down!

631
00:37:55,298 --> 00:37:57,823
- Oh! Ooh!
- Ooh!

632
00:37:57,900 --> 00:37:59,302
Ha ha ha!

633
00:37:59,435 --> 00:38:01,869
You can't keep
doing this, Forrest.

634
00:38:01,937 --> 00:38:04,371
You can't keep
trying to rescue me.

635
00:38:04,440 --> 00:38:06,237
They was trying to grab you.

636
00:38:06,309 --> 00:38:08,641
A lot of people try to grab me.

637
00:38:08,711 --> 00:38:12,704
Just... You can't keep
doing this all the time.

638
00:38:12,782 --> 00:38:16,309
I can't help it.
I love you.

639
00:38:16,385 --> 00:38:18,649
Forrest...

640
00:38:18,721 --> 00:38:20,689
You don't know what love is.

641
00:38:27,430 --> 00:38:30,365
You remember that time
we prayed, Forrest?

642
00:38:31,767 --> 00:38:35,203
We prayed for God
to turn me into a bird

643
00:38:35,271 --> 00:38:37,205
so I could fly far away.

644
00:38:38,441 --> 00:38:40,033
Yes, I do.

645
00:38:43,012 --> 00:38:45,446
You think I could
fly off this bridge?

646
00:38:52,688 --> 00:38:55,714
What do you mean, Jenny?

647
00:38:58,894 --> 00:39:00,156
Nothing.

648
00:39:03,232 --> 00:39:05,496
I got to get out of here.

649
00:39:07,737 --> 00:39:08,829
Wait, Jenny.

650
00:39:08,904 --> 00:39:11,338
Forrest, you stay
away from me, O.K.?

651
00:39:11,407 --> 00:39:13,341
You stay away from me, please.

652
00:39:13,409 --> 00:39:14,842
Can I have a ride?

653
00:39:14,910 --> 00:39:16,172
Where are you going?

654
00:39:16,245 --> 00:39:17,337
I don't care.

655
00:39:17,413 --> 00:39:18,641
Get in the truck.

656
00:39:18,714 --> 00:39:20,909
So bye-bye, Jenny.

657
00:39:22,318 --> 00:39:25,185
They sending me to Vietnam.

658
00:39:26,889 --> 00:39:29,722
It's this whole other country.

659
00:39:32,294 --> 00:39:34,057
Just hang on a minute.

660
00:39:35,631 --> 00:39:38,566
Listen, you promise me
something, O.K.?

661
00:39:38,634 --> 00:39:40,568
Just if you're
ever in trouble,

662
00:39:40,636 --> 00:39:41,898
don't be brave.

663
00:39:41,971 --> 00:39:44,906
You just run, O.K.?
Just run away.

664
00:39:44,974 --> 00:39:46,339
O.K.

665
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:52,843
Jenny.

666
00:39:54,417 --> 00:39:57,511
I'll write you all the time.

667
00:40:06,095 --> 00:40:09,693
<i>And just like that,
she was gone.</i>

668
00:40:24,947 --> 00:40:27,381
You come back safe to me.

669
00:40:27,449 --> 00:40:28,882
Do you hear?

670
00:40:48,470 --> 00:40:50,062
~ Some folks are born ~

671
00:40:50,138 --> 00:40:52,402
~ Made to wave the flag ~

672
00:40:52,474 --> 00:40:55,739
~ Ooh, they're red,
white, and blue ~

673
00:40:55,811 --> 00:40:59,338
~ And when the band plays
"Hail To The Chief" ~

674
00:40:59,414 --> 00:41:03,009
~ Ooh, they'll point
the cannon at you ~

675
00:41:03,085 --> 00:41:06,854
~ It ain't me ~

676
00:41:06,922 --> 00:41:10,016
~ I ain't no senator's son ~

677
00:41:10,092 --> 00:41:11,855
~ It ain't me ~

678
00:41:11,927 --> 00:41:13,360
<i>Now they told us</i>

679
00:41:13,428 --> 00:41:16,363
<i>that Vietnam was going
to be very different</i>

680
00:41:16,431 --> 00:41:18,456
<i>from the United States
of America.</i>

681
00:41:18,533 --> 00:41:22,629
<i>Except for all
the beer cans and barbecues,</i>

682
00:41:22,704 --> 00:41:24,467
<i>it was.</i>

683
00:41:34,216 --> 00:41:37,310
Hey, I'll bet there's shrimp
all in these waters.

684
00:41:37,386 --> 00:41:40,321
They tell me these Vietnams
is good shrimp.

685
00:41:40,389 --> 00:41:42,323
After we win this war

686
00:41:42,391 --> 00:41:44,018
and we take over everything,

687
00:41:44,092 --> 00:41:46,356
we can get American
shrimpers out here

688
00:41:46,428 --> 00:41:47,690
and shrimp these waters.

689
00:41:47,763 --> 00:41:49,697
Just shrimp all the time, man.

690
00:41:52,434 --> 00:41:54,698
You must be my FNGs.

691
00:41:54,770 --> 00:41:55,862
Morning, sir.

692
00:41:55,937 --> 00:41:57,461
Oh, get your hands down.

693
00:41:57,539 --> 00:41:58,972
Do not salute me.

694
00:41:59,041 --> 00:42:01,475
There are goddamn snipers
all around this area

695
00:42:01,543 --> 00:42:03,636
who'd love
to grease an officer.

696
00:42:03,712 --> 00:42:06,977
I'm Lieutenant Dan Taylor.
Welcome to Fort Platoon.

697
00:42:08,216 --> 00:42:09,808
What's wrong with your lip?

698
00:42:10,886 --> 00:42:13,150
I was born with big gums, sir.

699
00:42:13,221 --> 00:42:15,314
Well, you better tuck that in.

700
00:42:15,390 --> 00:42:17,824
Gonna get that caught
on a trip wire.

701
00:42:19,061 --> 00:42:21,495
Where are you boys
from in the world?

702
00:42:21,563 --> 00:42:22,655
- Alabama, sir!
- Alabama, sir!

703
00:42:23,899 --> 00:42:24,866
You twins?

704
00:42:27,102 --> 00:42:29,696
No. We are not relations, sir.

705
00:42:31,773 --> 00:42:33,035
Look,

706
00:42:33,108 --> 00:42:34,439
it's pretty basic here.

707
00:42:35,510 --> 00:42:36,772
You stick with me

708
00:42:36,845 --> 00:42:38,278
and learn from the guys

709
00:42:38,346 --> 00:42:40,280
who've been in country a while,

710
00:42:40,348 --> 00:42:41,610
you'll be all right.

711
00:42:41,683 --> 00:42:43,947
There is one item of G.I. Gear

712
00:42:44,019 --> 00:42:47,113
that can be the difference
between life and death...

713
00:42:47,189 --> 00:42:48,247
Socks.

714
00:42:48,323 --> 00:42:50,348
Cushioned sole, O.D. Green.

715
00:42:50,425 --> 00:42:52,256
Try and keep your feet dry.

716
00:42:52,327 --> 00:42:54,761
When we're out humpin',
change your socks

717
00:42:54,830 --> 00:42:56,024
whenever we stop.

718
00:42:56,098 --> 00:42:58,362
The Mekong will eat
a grunt's feet

719
00:42:58,433 --> 00:42:59,866
right off his legs.

720
00:42:59,935 --> 00:43:01,368
Sergeant Sims. God damn it,

721
00:43:01,436 --> 00:43:03,870
where's that sling rope
I said to order?

722
00:43:03,939 --> 00:43:05,372
I put in the requisitions.

723
00:43:05,440 --> 00:43:07,704
Well, you call
those sons of bitches...

724
00:43:07,776 --> 00:43:09,869
<i>Lieutenant Dan
sure knew his stuff.</i>

725
00:43:09,945 --> 00:43:12,880
<i>I felt real lucky
he was my lieutenant.</i>

726
00:43:12,948 --> 00:43:16,611
<i>He was from a long,
great military tradition.</i>

727
00:43:16,685 --> 00:43:19,210
<i>Somebody in his family
had fought</i>

728
00:43:19,287 --> 00:43:20,754
<i>and died</i>

729
00:43:20,822 --> 00:43:22,414
<i>in every...</i>

730
00:43:22,491 --> 00:43:23,617
<i>single...</i>

731
00:43:23,692 --> 00:43:25,785
<i>American war.</i>

732
00:43:25,861 --> 00:43:27,795
God damn it, kick some ass.

733
00:43:27,863 --> 00:43:29,125
Get on it!

734
00:43:29,197 --> 00:43:30,630
<i>I guess you could say</i>

735
00:43:30,699 --> 00:43:33,133
<i>he had a lot to live up to.</i>

736
00:43:34,202 --> 00:43:36,136
So, you boys
from Arkansas, huh?

737
00:43:36,204 --> 00:43:37,296
Well,

738
00:43:37,372 --> 00:43:39,135
I been through there.

739
00:43:39,207 --> 00:43:41,971
Little Rock's a fine town.

740
00:43:42,043 --> 00:43:43,806
Now, shake down your gear.

741
00:43:43,879 --> 00:43:45,141
See the platoon sergeant.

742
00:43:45,213 --> 00:43:47,977
Draw what you need
for the field.

743
00:43:48,049 --> 00:43:49,482
If you boys are hungry,

744
00:43:49,551 --> 00:43:52,315
we got steaks burning
right over here.

745
00:43:52,387 --> 00:43:55,151
Two standing orders
in this platoon...

746
00:43:55,223 --> 00:43:57,748
1... take care of your feet,

747
00:43:57,826 --> 00:44:01,421
2... try not to do
anything stupid,

748
00:44:01,496 --> 00:44:03,088
like getting
yourself killed.

749
00:44:09,337 --> 00:44:11,862
I sure hope I don't
let him down.

750
00:44:23,051 --> 00:44:25,986
<i>I got to see
a lot of the countryside.</i>

751
00:44:26,054 --> 00:44:28,454
<i>We would take
these real long walks.</i>

752
00:44:30,525 --> 00:44:32,459
~ There must be
some kind of way ~

753
00:44:32,527 --> 00:44:34,620
~ Out of here ~

754
00:44:34,696 --> 00:44:36,789
~ Said the joker
to the thief ~

755
00:44:36,865 --> 00:44:38,298
<i>And we were always lookin'</i>

756
00:44:38,366 --> 00:44:40,300
<i>for this guy named Charlie.</i>

757
00:44:40,368 --> 00:44:41,960
~ There's too much confusion ~

758
00:44:43,371 --> 00:44:46,135
~ I can't get no relief ~

759
00:44:48,710 --> 00:44:49,802
Hold it up!

760
00:44:49,878 --> 00:44:51,311
Hold up, boys!

761
00:44:52,881 --> 00:44:55,907
<i>It wasn't always fun.</i>

762
00:44:55,984 --> 00:44:59,249
<i>Lieutenant Dan was always
getting these funny feelings</i>

763
00:44:59,321 --> 00:45:02,415
<i>about a rock or a trail
or the road,</i>

764
00:45:02,490 --> 00:45:05,425
<i>so he'd tell us
to get down, shut up.</i>

765
00:45:05,493 --> 00:45:06,585
Get down!

766
00:45:06,661 --> 00:45:07,753
Shut up!

767
00:45:08,830 --> 00:45:10,092
<i>So we did.</i>

768
00:45:26,615 --> 00:45:29,880
<i>Now I don't know
much about anything,</i>

769
00:45:29,951 --> 00:45:32,886
<i>but I think some of
America's best young men</i>

770
00:45:32,954 --> 00:45:34,216
<i>served in this war.</i>

771
00:45:34,289 --> 00:45:36,553
<i>There was Dallas from Phoenix.</i>

772
00:45:37,959 --> 00:45:40,723
<i>Cleveland...
he was from Detroit.</i>

773
00:45:40,795 --> 00:45:43,587
Hey, Tex.

774
00:45:43,665 --> 00:45:45,257
What the hell's going on?

775
00:45:45,333 --> 00:45:47,528
<i>And Tex was...</i>

776
00:45:47,602 --> 00:45:50,196
<i>Well, I don't remember
where Tex come from...</i>

777
00:45:50,272 --> 00:45:51,796
Ah, nothing.

778
00:45:55,710 --> 00:45:57,735
Fourth platoon, on your feet.

779
00:45:57,812 --> 00:46:00,713
Y'all got 10 clicks
to go to that river.

780
00:46:00,782 --> 00:46:02,374
Move out.

781
00:46:02,450 --> 00:46:04,884
1, 2! Hup!

782
00:46:06,288 --> 00:46:07,721
Step it up!

783
00:46:07,789 --> 00:46:09,120
Look alive out there.

784
00:46:09,190 --> 00:46:10,623
<i>The good thing about Vietnam</i>

785
00:46:10,692 --> 00:46:12,956
<i>is there was always
someplace to go.</i>

786
00:46:13,028 --> 00:46:14,290
Fire in the hole!

787
00:46:17,866 --> 00:46:20,460
Gump, check out that hole.

788
00:46:20,535 --> 00:46:23,470
<i>And there was always
something to do.</i>

789
00:46:23,538 --> 00:46:24,630
Mount 'em up!

790
00:46:24,706 --> 00:46:26,503
Spread out!
Cover his back!

791
00:46:31,579 --> 00:46:34,173
<i>One day it started raining,</i>

792
00:46:34,249 --> 00:46:37,582
<i>and it didn't quit for four months.</i>

793
00:46:37,652 --> 00:46:41,088
<i>We've been through
every kind of rain there is...</i>

794
00:46:41,156 --> 00:46:43,784
<i>little bitty stinging rain</i>

795
00:46:43,858 --> 00:46:47,760
<i>and big old fat rain,</i>

796
00:46:47,829 --> 00:46:50,630
<i>rain that flew in sideways,</i>

797
00:46:50,763 --> 00:46:52,424
<i>and sometimes rain even seemed</i>

798
00:46:52,498 --> 00:46:55,831
<i>to come straight up
from underneath.</i>

799
00:46:55,901 --> 00:46:59,428
<i>Shoot, it even rained at night.</i>

800
00:46:59,505 --> 00:47:01,268
Hey, Forrest.

801
00:47:01,340 --> 00:47:02,432
Hey, Bubba.

802
00:47:02,508 --> 00:47:04,772
I'm going to lean up against you.

803
00:47:04,844 --> 00:47:06,277
You lean up against me.

804
00:47:06,345 --> 00:47:08,609
This way we don't have to sleep

805
00:47:08,681 --> 00:47:10,615
with our heads in the mud.

806
00:47:10,683 --> 00:47:13,277
You know why we're
a good partnership, Forrest?

807
00:47:13,352 --> 00:47:16,617
'Cause we be watching out
for one another,

808
00:47:16,689 --> 00:47:18,452
like brothers and stuff.

809
00:47:20,359 --> 00:47:21,951
Hey, Forrest,

810
00:47:22,028 --> 00:47:24,121
something I been thinking about.

811
00:47:24,196 --> 00:47:27,131
I got a very important
question to ask you.

812
00:47:28,868 --> 00:47:30,802
How would you like to go

813
00:47:30,870 --> 00:47:32,804
into the shrimping
business with me?

814
00:47:34,373 --> 00:47:35,635
O.K.

815
00:47:35,708 --> 00:47:37,471
Man, I tell you what.

816
00:47:37,543 --> 00:47:39,807
I got it all figured out, too.

817
00:47:39,879 --> 00:47:41,312
So many pounds of shrimp

818
00:47:41,380 --> 00:47:42,813
will pay off the boat.

819
00:47:42,882 --> 00:47:44,315
So many pounds for gas.

820
00:47:44,383 --> 00:47:46,317
We'll live right on the boat.

821
00:47:46,385 --> 00:47:48,649
We ain't got to pay no rent.

822
00:47:48,721 --> 00:47:50,655
We can just work it together,

823
00:47:50,723 --> 00:47:52,657
split everything right
down the middle.

824
00:47:52,725 --> 00:47:54,818
Man, I'm telling you, 50-50.

825
00:47:54,894 --> 00:47:57,920
Hey, Forrest,
all the shrimp you can eat.

826
00:47:59,498 --> 00:48:02,092
That's a fine idea.

827
00:48:02,168 --> 00:48:04,932
<i>Bubba did have a fine idea.</i>

828
00:48:08,340 --> 00:48:09,602
<i>I even wrote Jenny</i>

829
00:48:09,675 --> 00:48:11,609
<i>and told her all about it.</i>

830
00:48:11,677 --> 00:48:13,269
<i>I sent her letters...</i>

831
00:48:13,345 --> 00:48:15,438
<i>Not every day, but almost.</i>

832
00:48:15,514 --> 00:48:17,778
<i>I told her what I was doing</i>

833
00:48:17,850 --> 00:48:20,284
<i>and asked her what she was doing</i>

834
00:48:20,352 --> 00:48:23,588
<i>and told her how
I thought about her always.</i>

835
00:48:24,956 --> 00:48:26,890
<i>And how I was looking forward</i>

836
00:48:26,958 --> 00:48:28,892
<i>to getting a letter from her</i>

837
00:48:28,960 --> 00:48:31,724
<i>just as soon
as she had the time.</i>

838
00:48:31,796 --> 00:48:34,731
<i>I'd always let her know
that I was O.K.</i>

839
00:48:34,799 --> 00:48:42,228
<i>Then I'd sign each letter
"Love, Forrest Gump."</i>

840
00:48:52,149 --> 00:48:54,913
~ There's somethin'
happenin' here ~

841
00:48:56,253 --> 00:48:59,848
<i>This one day, we was out
walking like always,</i>

842
00:48:59,924 --> 00:49:03,690
<i>and then, just like that,</i>

843
00:49:03,761 --> 00:49:05,695
<i>somebody turned off the rain,</i>

844
00:49:05,763 --> 00:49:07,355
<i>and the sun come out.</i>

845
00:49:07,431 --> 00:49:10,195
~ I got to beware ~

846
00:49:10,267 --> 00:49:12,360
Ambush!

847
00:49:12,436 --> 00:49:14,370
Take cover!

848
00:49:22,947 --> 00:49:25,616
Get that pig up here,
god damn it!

849
00:49:25,749 --> 00:49:27,876
Forrest! You okay?

850
00:49:30,487 --> 00:49:33,388
Strong-arm, Strong-arm!

851
00:49:33,457 --> 00:49:36,255
Hey! We got a man down!

852
00:49:36,326 --> 00:49:39,784
Strong-arm,
this is Leg Lima 6! Over!

853
00:49:39,863 --> 00:49:42,297
Roger, Strong-arm!
Be advised we have incoming

854
00:49:42,366 --> 00:49:44,766
from the treeline at point blue

855
00:49:44,835 --> 00:49:47,167
plus two!
A.K.S and rockets!

856
00:49:47,237 --> 00:49:48,499
We're getting it hard!

857
00:49:48,572 --> 00:49:50,130
Misfire! Misfire!

858
00:49:51,208 --> 00:49:53,005
God damn it!

859
00:49:54,578 --> 00:49:58,514
Get that pig unfucked
and on the treeline!

860
00:50:00,350 --> 00:50:02,944
They got us,
and it hurt.

861
00:50:03,020 --> 00:50:06,512
We're going to move
back to the blue line.

862
00:50:06,590 --> 00:50:09,491
Pull back! Pull back!

863
00:50:09,559 --> 00:50:11,550
Forrest! Run, Forrest!

864
00:50:11,628 --> 00:50:13,357
Pull back!

865
00:50:13,430 --> 00:50:15,625
Run! Run, man!

866
00:50:15,699 --> 00:50:16,791
Run!

867
00:50:16,867 --> 00:50:18,129
Pull back, Gump!

868
00:50:19,703 --> 00:50:22,866
Run, God damn it! Run!

869
00:50:48,799 --> 00:50:52,826
<i>I ran and ran
just like Jenny told me to.</i>

870
00:50:55,572 --> 00:50:57,767
<i>I ran so far so fast</i>

871
00:50:57,841 --> 00:51:00,275
<i>that pretty soon
I was all by myself,</i>

872
00:51:00,343 --> 00:51:01,935
<i>which was a bad thing.</i>

873
00:51:02,012 --> 00:51:03,104
Bubba.

874
00:51:05,682 --> 00:51:07,775
<i>Bubba was my best good friend.</i>

875
00:51:07,851 --> 00:51:10,285
<i>I had to make sure he was O.K.</i>

876
00:51:19,362 --> 00:51:21,796
Where the hell are you?

877
00:51:21,865 --> 00:51:23,958
Bubba!

878
00:51:24,034 --> 00:51:26,969
<i>And on my way
back to find Bubba,</i>

879
00:51:27,037 --> 00:51:29,801
<i>well, there was this boy
laying on the ground.</i>

880
00:51:29,873 --> 00:51:30,862
Tex.

881
00:51:32,809 --> 00:51:34,401
O.K.

882
00:51:34,478 --> 00:51:36,912
<i>I couldn't let him
lay there all alone,</i>

883
00:51:36,980 --> 00:51:38,413
<i>scared the way he was,</i>

884
00:51:38,482 --> 00:51:40,245
<i>so I grabbed him up</i>

885
00:51:40,317 --> 00:51:42,046
<i>and run him out of there.</i>

886
00:51:57,267 --> 00:51:59,997
<i>Every time I went back
looking for Bubba,</i>

887
00:52:00,070 --> 00:52:01,503
<i>somebody else was saying,</i>

888
00:52:01,571 --> 00:52:04,506
<i>"Help me, Forrest, help me!"</i>

889
00:52:11,081 --> 00:52:13,242
O.K. Here. Here.

890
00:52:15,552 --> 00:52:18,521
No sweat, man.
Lay back. You'll be O.K.

891
00:52:20,924 --> 00:52:25,384
<i>I started to get scared
that I might never find Bubba.</i>

892
00:52:25,462 --> 00:52:26,895
I know my position

893
00:52:26,963 --> 00:52:28,863
is danger close!

894
00:52:28,932 --> 00:52:31,366
We got Charlie
all over this area.

895
00:52:31,434 --> 00:52:34,369
I got to have those fast movers
in here now. Over.

896
00:52:34,437 --> 00:52:36,871
Lieutenant Dan,
Coleman's dead!

897
00:52:36,940 --> 00:52:38,373
I know he's dead!

898
00:52:38,441 --> 00:52:41,376
My whole goddamn platoon
is wiped out!

899
00:52:41,444 --> 00:52:42,877
God damn it!

900
00:52:42,946 --> 00:52:44,880
What are you doing?

901
00:52:44,948 --> 00:52:46,381
You leave me here!

902
00:52:46,449 --> 00:52:48,383
Get away.
Just leave me here!

903
00:52:48,451 --> 00:52:49,884
Get out!

904
00:52:49,953 --> 00:52:53,889
Aah! God, I said
leave me here, God damn it!

905
00:52:53,957 --> 00:52:56,323
<i>Leg Lima, this is Strong-arm.</i>

906
00:52:56,393 --> 00:52:59,362
<i>Be advised your fast movers
are inbound. Over.</i>

907
00:52:59,429 --> 00:53:02,830
<i>Then it felt like something
just jumped up and bit me.</i>

908
00:53:02,899 --> 00:53:05,663
Aah! Something bit me!

909
00:53:09,406 --> 00:53:12,500
Aah! Aah!

910
00:53:12,576 --> 00:53:14,510
You son of a bitch!

911
00:53:14,578 --> 00:53:15,909
Aah!

912
00:53:15,979 --> 00:53:19,005
I can't leave the platoon.

913
00:53:19,082 --> 00:53:22,017
I told you
to leave me there, Gump.

914
00:53:22,085 --> 00:53:24,053
Forget about me.
Get yourself out!

915
00:53:24,120 --> 00:53:26,350
Did you hear what I said?

916
00:53:26,423 --> 00:53:28,857
Gump, damn it, put me down.

917
00:53:28,925 --> 00:53:31,450
Get your ass out of here.

918
00:53:33,430 --> 00:53:36,558
I didn't ask you to pull me out
of there, God damn you!

919
00:53:36,633 --> 00:53:39,568
Where the hell
do you think you're going?

920
00:53:39,636 --> 00:53:41,069
To get Bubba.

921
00:53:41,137 --> 00:53:44,072
I got an air strike
inbound right now.

922
00:53:44,140 --> 00:53:46,631
They're going to nape
the whole area.

923
00:53:46,710 --> 00:53:48,177
Stay here!
That's an order.

924
00:53:48,245 --> 00:53:49,678
I gotta find Bubba!

925
00:54:04,895 --> 00:54:06,590
Forrest.

926
00:54:13,904 --> 00:54:15,235
Bubba.

927
00:54:15,305 --> 00:54:17,136
I'm O.K., Forrest.

928
00:54:17,207 --> 00:54:18,731
I'm O.K.

929
00:54:27,150 --> 00:54:29,175
O-Oh, Bubba, no.

930
00:54:29,252 --> 00:54:31,049
I'll be all right.

931
00:54:39,429 --> 00:54:40,521
Come on.

932
00:54:40,597 --> 00:54:42,326
Come on. Come on.

933
00:54:46,303 --> 00:54:48,999
Ugh. I'm O.K., Forrest.

934
00:54:51,942 --> 00:54:53,876
I'm O.K. I'm fine.

935
00:55:30,380 --> 00:55:33,406
Top smoke. Get it up there.

936
00:55:33,483 --> 00:55:36,350
<i>If I'd have known
this was going to be</i>

937
00:55:36,419 --> 00:55:39,354
<i>the last time
me and Bubba was gonna talk,</i>

938
00:55:39,422 --> 00:55:42,357
<i>I'd of thought of
something better to say.</i>

939
00:55:42,425 --> 00:55:43,483
Hey, Bubba.

940
00:55:43,560 --> 00:55:44,822
Hey, Forrest.

941
00:55:47,263 --> 00:55:48,696
Forrest...

942
00:55:48,765 --> 00:55:51,859
Why did this happen?

943
00:55:51,935 --> 00:55:54,870
You got shot.

944
00:55:54,938 --> 00:55:59,307
<i>Then Bubba said something
I won't ever forget.</i>

945
00:55:59,376 --> 00:56:02,937
I want to go home.

946
00:56:03,013 --> 00:56:05,811
<i>Bubba was my best good friend.</i>

947
00:56:05,882 --> 00:56:07,816
<i>And even I know</i>

948
00:56:07,884 --> 00:56:11,320
<i>that ain't something you can
find just around the corner.</i>

949
00:56:11,388 --> 00:56:14,824
<i>Bubba was going to be
a shrimping boat captain,</i>

950
00:56:14,891 --> 00:56:19,191
<i>but instead, he died right there
by that river in Vietnam.</i>

951
00:56:24,768 --> 00:56:27,100
That's all I have
to say about that.

952
00:56:29,305 --> 00:56:31,500
It was a bullet, wasn't it?

953
00:56:33,410 --> 00:56:34,843
A bullet?

954
00:56:34,911 --> 00:56:37,641
That jumped up and bit you.

955
00:56:38,782 --> 00:56:40,647
Oh. Yes, sir.

956
00:56:40,717 --> 00:56:43,345
Bit me directly
in the but-tocks.

957
00:56:43,420 --> 00:56:47,857
They said it was a million
dollar wound, but...

958
00:56:47,924 --> 00:56:49,858
the army must keep that money,

959
00:56:49,926 --> 00:56:53,862
'cause I still ain't seen a nickel
of that million dollars.

960
00:56:53,930 --> 00:56:57,733
The only good thing about being
wounded in the but-tocks

961
00:56:57,866 --> 00:56:59,629
<i>is the ice cream.</i>

962
00:56:59,701 --> 00:57:02,602
<i>They gave me all
the ice cream I could eat.</i>

963
00:57:02,671 --> 00:57:04,104
<i>And guess what?</i>

964
00:57:04,172 --> 00:57:08,074
<i>A good friend of mine was
in the bed right next door.</i>

965
00:57:09,377 --> 00:57:12,437
Lieutenant Dan,
I got you some ice cream.

966
00:57:14,316 --> 00:57:17,046
Lieutenant Dan, ice cream!

967
00:57:27,896 --> 00:57:30,660
It's time for
your bath, Lieutenant.

968
00:57:38,907 --> 00:57:40,306
Harper!

969
00:57:43,912 --> 00:57:45,345
Cooper.

970
00:57:45,413 --> 00:57:46,345
Larson.

971
00:57:48,416 --> 00:57:49,678
Webster.

972
00:57:50,919 --> 00:57:52,352
Gump.

973
00:57:52,420 --> 00:57:53,853
Gump!

974
00:57:53,922 --> 00:57:55,549
I'm Forrest Gump.

975
00:57:57,859 --> 00:57:59,258
Kyle.

976
00:58:00,862 --> 00:58:02,193
Nichols.

977
00:58:03,932 --> 00:58:06,298
McMill.

978
00:58:06,368 --> 00:58:07,357
Johnson.

979
00:58:18,479 --> 00:58:21,448
<i>Surprise, surprise, surprise!</i>

980
00:58:24,251 --> 00:58:27,687
Gump, how can you
watch that stupid shit?

981
00:58:27,755 --> 00:58:29,188
Turn it off.

982
00:58:29,256 --> 00:58:31,690
<i>You are tuned
to the American forces</i>

983
00:58:31,759 --> 00:58:33,192
<i>Vietnam network.</i>

984
00:58:33,260 --> 00:58:34,818
<i>This is channel 6, Saigon.</i>

985
00:58:37,264 --> 00:58:38,925
Good catch, Gump.

986
00:58:40,768 --> 00:58:42,668
You know how to play this?

987
00:58:44,271 --> 00:58:46,739
Come on. Let me show you.

988
00:58:48,275 --> 00:58:50,709
Now, the secret to this game is

989
00:58:50,778 --> 00:58:52,712
no matter what happens,

990
00:58:52,780 --> 00:58:55,214
never, ever...

991
00:58:55,282 --> 00:58:57,375
take your eye off the ball.

992
00:59:00,287 --> 00:59:01,549
All right.

993
00:59:04,792 --> 00:59:06,225
<i>For some reason,</i>

994
00:59:06,293 --> 00:59:08,727
<i>Ping-Pong came very natural to me.</i>

995
00:59:08,796 --> 00:59:09,956
See?

996
00:59:10,030 --> 00:59:12,225
Any idiot can play.

997
00:59:12,299 --> 00:59:15,735
<i>So I started playing it
all the time.</i>

998
00:59:15,803 --> 00:59:17,430
<i>I played Ping-Pong</i>

999
00:59:17,505 --> 00:59:21,100
<i>even when I didn't have anyone
to play Ping-Pong with.</i>

1000
00:59:29,450 --> 00:59:30,883
<i>The hospital's people</i>

1001
00:59:30,951 --> 00:59:34,887
<i>said it made me look
like a duck in water...</i>

1002
00:59:34,955 --> 00:59:36,388
<i>Whatever that means.</i>

1003
00:59:36,457 --> 00:59:39,688
<i>Even Lieutenant Dan
would come and watch me play.</i>

1004
00:59:44,464 --> 00:59:46,898
<i>I played Ping-Pong so much,</i>

1005
00:59:46,966 --> 00:59:49,799
