a little white lie,

1501
01:28:01,820 --> 01:28:03,754
so it wasn't hurting nobody.

1502
01:28:03,822 --> 01:28:06,256
So anyway,
I'm putting all that

1503
01:28:06,325 --> 01:28:08,759
on gas, ropes, and new nets

1504
01:28:08,827 --> 01:28:11,762
and a brand-new shrimping boat.

1505
01:28:32,885 --> 01:28:36,321
<i>Now Bubba told me everything
he knew about shrimping,</i>

1506
01:28:36,388 --> 01:28:39,323
<i>but you know what I found out?</i>

1507
01:28:40,392 --> 01:28:42,952
<i>Shrimping is tough.</i>

1508
01:28:44,897 --> 01:28:47,559
I only caught five.

1509
01:28:47,633 --> 01:28:51,069
A couple more,
you can have yourself a cocktail.

1510
01:28:52,905 --> 01:28:55,840
Hey, you ever think about
naming this old boat?

1511
01:28:55,908 --> 01:28:58,843
It's bad luck to have
a boat without a name.

1512
01:28:58,911 --> 01:29:01,345
<i>I'd never named a boat before,</i>

1513
01:29:01,413 --> 01:29:06,441
<i>but there was only one
I could think of,</i>

1514
01:29:06,518 --> 01:29:10,477
<i>the most beautiful name
in the wide world.</i>

1515
01:29:14,560 --> 01:29:16,050
<i>~ Do a little dance ~</i>

1516
01:29:16,128 --> 01:29:18,096
<i>~ Make a little love ~</i>

1517
01:29:18,163 --> 01:29:22,463
<i>~ Get down tonight ~</i>

1518
01:29:22,534 --> 01:29:24,729
<i>~ Do a little dance ~</i>

1519
01:29:24,803 --> 01:29:26,566
<i>~ Make a little love ~</i>

1520
01:29:26,638 --> 01:29:28,265
<i>~ Get down tonight ~</i>

1521
01:29:28,340 --> 01:29:29,432
<i>~ Whoo ~</i>

1522
01:29:29,508 --> 01:29:30,805
<i>~ Get down tonight... ~</i>

1523
01:29:30,876 --> 01:29:33,276
<i>Now, I hadn't heard from Jenny</i>

1524
01:29:33,345 --> 01:29:34,642
<i>in a long while,</i>

1525
01:29:34,713 --> 01:29:37,147
<i>but I thought about her a lot.</i>

1526
01:29:37,216 --> 01:29:40,310
<i>I hoped whatever
she was doing made her happy.</i>

1527
01:29:40,385 --> 01:29:45,413
~ Oh, and the bird
you cannot change ~

1528
01:29:48,861 --> 01:29:55,562
~ And this bird
you cannot change ~

1529
01:29:55,634 --> 01:30:03,006
~ Lord knows I can't change ~

1530
01:30:03,075 --> 01:30:10,004
~ Lord, help me, I can't change ~

1531
01:31:26,224 --> 01:31:29,660
<i>I thought about Jenny all the time.</i>

1532
01:31:52,984 --> 01:31:55,077
Hey!

1533
01:32:18,610 --> 01:32:23,206
Lieutenant Dan,
what are you doing here?

1534
01:32:23,281 --> 01:32:26,648
Well, thought
I'd try out my sea legs.

1535
01:32:26,718 --> 01:32:29,653
Well, you ain't got no legs,
Lieutenant Dan.

1536
01:32:29,721 --> 01:32:31,154
Yes, I know that.

1537
01:32:31,222 --> 01:32:35,420
You wrote me a letter,
you idiot.

1538
01:32:35,493 --> 01:32:37,859
Well, well.
Captain Forrest Gump.

1539
01:32:37,929 --> 01:32:40,796
I had to see this for myself...

1540
01:32:42,100 --> 01:32:43,567
and...

1541
01:32:43,635 --> 01:32:48,072
I told you if you were ever
a shrimp boat captain,

1542
01:32:48,139 --> 01:32:50,073
that I'd be your first mate.

1543
01:32:50,141 --> 01:32:51,802
Well, here I am.

1544
01:32:51,876 --> 01:32:53,810
I'm a man of my word.

1545
01:32:53,878 --> 01:32:54,902
O.K.

1546
01:32:54,979 --> 01:32:57,140
But don't you be thinking

1547
01:32:57,215 --> 01:32:59,649
that I'm going
to be calling you "sir."

1548
01:32:59,717 --> 01:33:00,649
No, sir.

1549
01:33:09,193 --> 01:33:10,717
It's my boat.

1550
01:33:13,898 --> 01:33:17,994
I have a feeling
if we head due east,

1551
01:33:18,069 --> 01:33:21,630
we'll find some shrimp,
so take a left.

1552
01:33:23,041 --> 01:33:24,474
Take a left!

1553
01:33:24,542 --> 01:33:25,474
Which way?

1554
01:33:25,543 --> 01:33:26,475
Over there!

1555
01:33:26,544 --> 01:33:27,977
They're over there!

1556
01:33:28,046 --> 01:33:31,379
Get on the wheel
and take a left.

1557
01:33:31,449 --> 01:33:32,882
O.K.

1558
01:33:34,218 --> 01:33:36,152
Gump, what are you doing?

1559
01:33:36,220 --> 01:33:37,653
Take a left!

1560
01:33:37,722 --> 01:33:38,711
Left!

1561
01:33:40,591 --> 01:33:44,527
That's where we're going
to find those shrimp, my boy!

1562
01:33:44,595 --> 01:33:45,527
Ha ha!

1563
01:33:45,596 --> 01:33:47,723
That's where we'll find them.

1564
01:34:00,144 --> 01:34:02,078
Still no shrimp, Lieutenant Dan.

1565
01:34:02,146 --> 01:34:04,080
O.K., so I was wrong.

1566
01:34:04,148 --> 01:34:07,083
Well, how are we
going to find them?

1567
01:34:07,151 --> 01:34:11,178
Maybe you should
just pray for shrimp.

1568
01:34:11,255 --> 01:34:13,917
~ So pray that ~

1569
01:34:13,992 --> 01:34:17,257
~ I'm homeward bound... ~

1570
01:34:17,328 --> 01:34:20,024
<i>So I went to church every Sunday.</i>

1571
01:34:21,466 --> 01:34:23,400
<i>Sometimes Lieutenant Dan came, too,</i>

1572
01:34:23,468 --> 01:34:27,336
<i>though I think he left
the praying up to me.</i>

1573
01:34:41,853 --> 01:34:43,252
No shrimp.

1574
01:34:44,355 --> 01:34:47,290
Where the hell's
this God of yours?

1575
01:34:47,358 --> 01:34:49,792
<i>It's funny Lieutenant Dan said that</i>

1576
01:34:49,861 --> 01:34:53,731
<i>'cause right then God showed up.</i>

1577
01:35:09,379 --> 01:35:11,813
You'll never sink this boat!

1578
01:35:11,882 --> 01:35:14,544
<i>Now, me, I was scared,</i>

1579
01:35:14,618 --> 01:35:18,679
<i>but Lieutenant Dan, he was mad.</i>

1580
01:35:18,756 --> 01:35:19,745
Come on!

1581
01:35:22,292 --> 01:35:24,590
You call this a storm?

1582
01:35:24,661 --> 01:35:28,597
Come on, you son of a bitch!

1583
01:35:28,665 --> 01:35:32,601
It's time for a showdown!

1584
01:35:32,669 --> 01:35:34,136
You and me!

1585
01:35:34,204 --> 01:35:37,264
I'm right here!
Come and get me!

1586
01:35:37,341 --> 01:35:39,866
Ha ha! Ha ha!

1587
01:35:39,943 --> 01:35:41,376
You'll never sink...

1588
01:35:41,445 --> 01:35:42,742
this...

1589
01:35:42,813 --> 01:35:43,905
boat!

1590
01:35:43,981 --> 01:35:45,915
Ha ha ha ha!

1591
01:35:45,983 --> 01:35:48,118
<i>Hurricane Carmen
came through here yesterday,</i>

1592
01:35:48,251 --> 01:35:50,048
destroying nearly
everything in its path.

1593
01:35:50,120 --> 01:35:53,055
And as in other towns
up and down the coast,

1594
01:35:53,123 --> 01:35:55,921
Bayou La Batre's
entire shrimping industry

1595
01:35:55,992 --> 01:35:58,324
<i>has fallen victim to Carmen</i>

1596
01:35:58,394 --> 01:36:01,227
<i>and has been left in utter ruin.</i>

1597
01:36:01,297 --> 01:36:02,730
<i>This reporter has learned,</i>

1598
01:36:02,799 --> 01:36:05,233
<i>in fact, only one shrimping boat</i>

1599
01:36:05,301 --> 01:36:06,825
<i>actually survived the storm.</i>

1600
01:36:06,903 --> 01:36:09,371
Louise. Louise, there's Forrest.

1601
01:36:09,439 --> 01:36:12,533
<i>After that, shrimping was easy.</i>

1602
01:36:12,609 --> 01:36:15,373
~ There will be great bounty ~

1603
01:36:15,445 --> 01:36:18,107
~ Oh, my God... ~

1604
01:36:18,181 --> 01:36:20,115
<i>Since people still
needed them shrimps</i>

1605
01:36:20,183 --> 01:36:22,549
<i>for shrimp cocktails
and barbecues and all</i>

1606
01:36:22,619 --> 01:36:25,554
and we were the only boat
left standing,

1607
01:36:25,622 --> 01:36:28,056
Bubba Gump shrimp's
what they got.

1608
01:36:28,124 --> 01:36:31,059
We got a whole bunch of boats.

1609
01:36:31,127 --> 01:36:33,061
<i>12 Jennys, big old warehouse.</i>

1610
01:36:33,129 --> 01:36:35,063
We even have hats

1611
01:36:35,131 --> 01:36:37,565
that say "Bubba Gump" on them.

1612
01:36:37,634 --> 01:36:39,067
Bubba Gump Shrimp.

1613
01:36:39,135 --> 01:36:40,568
It's a household name.

1614
01:36:40,637 --> 01:36:42,298
Hold on there, boy.

1615
01:36:42,372 --> 01:36:44,806
Are you telling me
you're the owner

1616
01:36:44,874 --> 01:36:47,104
of the Bubba Gump
Shrimp Corporation?

1617
01:36:47,177 --> 01:36:50,112
Yes. We got more money
than Davy Crockett.

1618
01:36:50,180 --> 01:36:53,115
Boy, I heard some whoppers
in my time,

1619
01:36:53,183 --> 01:36:56,118
but that tops them all.

1620
01:36:56,186 --> 01:36:58,154
Ha ha ha ha!

1621
01:36:58,221 --> 01:37:01,622
We were sitting
next to a millionaire.

1622
01:37:04,627 --> 01:37:09,621
Well, I thought it was
a very lovely story,

1623
01:37:09,699 --> 01:37:12,759
and you tell it so well,

1624
01:37:12,835 --> 01:37:14,928
with such enthusiasm.

1625
01:37:15,004 --> 01:37:19,100
Would you like to see
what Lieutenant Dan looks like?

1626
01:37:19,175 --> 01:37:21,405
Yes, I would.

1627
01:37:25,682 --> 01:37:27,309
That's him right there.

1628
01:37:29,552 --> 01:37:32,612
Let me tell you
something about Lieutenant Dan.

1629
01:37:32,689 --> 01:37:34,179
Forrest...

1630
01:37:39,362 --> 01:37:43,492
I never thanked you
for saving my life.

1631
01:38:08,691 --> 01:38:11,125
<i>He never actually said so,</i>

1632
01:38:11,194 --> 01:38:15,563
<i>but I think
he made his peace with God.</i>

1633
01:38:22,338 --> 01:38:25,136
<i>For the second time in 17 days,</i>

1634
01:38:25,208 --> 01:38:27,642
<i>President Ford escaped
possible assassination today.</i>

1635
01:38:27,710 --> 01:38:30,645
<i>Base to Jenny 1.
Base to Jenny 1.</i>

1636
01:38:30,713 --> 01:38:32,146
<i>Jenny 1. Go, Margo.</i>

1637
01:38:32,215 --> 01:38:34,149
<i>Forrest has a phone call.</i>

1638
01:38:34,217 --> 01:38:38,654
Yeah, well, you'll have
to tell them to call him back.

1639
01:38:38,721 --> 01:38:41,155
He is indisposed at the moment.

1640
01:38:41,224 --> 01:38:42,691
<i>His mama's sick.</i>

1641
01:39:01,778 --> 01:39:02,710
Where's Mama?

1642
01:39:02,779 --> 01:39:04,576
She's upstairs.

1643
01:39:07,016 --> 01:39:08,745
Hi, Forrest.

1644
01:39:09,819 --> 01:39:11,013
I'll see you tomorrow.

1645
01:39:11,087 --> 01:39:12,384
Oh, all right.

1646
01:39:18,761 --> 01:39:21,594
Sure got you straightened out,
didn't we, boy?

1647
01:39:33,776 --> 01:39:35,266
What's the matter, Mama?

1648
01:39:35,345 --> 01:39:38,508
I'm dying, Forrest.

1649
01:39:40,650 --> 01:39:43,551
Come on in,
sit down over here.

1650
01:39:57,266 --> 01:39:59,393
Why are you dying, Mama?

1651
01:39:59,469 --> 01:40:01,562
It's my time.

1652
01:40:01,637 --> 01:40:04,697
It's just my time.

1653
01:40:04,774 --> 01:40:06,799
Oh, now...

1654
01:40:07,877 --> 01:40:10,437
don't you be afraid,
sweetheart.

1655
01:40:10,513 --> 01:40:13,914
Death is just a part of life.

1656
01:40:13,983 --> 01:40:17,942
Something we're all
destined to do.

1657
01:40:18,020 --> 01:40:20,352
I didn't know it,

1658
01:40:20,423 --> 01:40:23,358
but I was destined
to be your mama.

1659
01:40:23,426 --> 01:40:26,156
I did the best I could.

1660
01:40:26,229 --> 01:40:28,163
You did good.

1661
01:40:28,231 --> 01:40:34,500
Well... I happen to believe
you make your own destiny.

1662
01:40:34,570 --> 01:40:39,098
You have to do the best
with what God gave you.

1663
01:40:42,612 --> 01:40:45,206
What's my destiny, Mama?

1664
01:40:45,281 --> 01:40:49,718
You're going to have
to figure that out for yourself.

1665
01:40:51,053 --> 01:40:53,988
Life is a box
of chocolates, Forrest.

1666
01:40:54,056 --> 01:40:56,991
You never know what
you're going to get.

1667
01:40:57,059 --> 01:40:59,994
<i>Mama always had a way
of explaining things</i>

1668
01:41:00,062 --> 01:41:01,996
<i>so I could understand them.</i>

1669
01:41:02,064 --> 01:41:03,531
I will miss you, Forrest.

1670
01:41:05,268 --> 01:41:07,532
<i>She had got the cancer</i>

1671
01:41:07,603 --> 01:41:09,537
<i>and died on a Tuesday.</i>

1672
01:41:09,605 --> 01:41:12,199
<i>I bought her a new hat</i>

1673
01:41:12,275 --> 01:41:14,300
<i>with little flowers on it.</i>

1674
01:41:17,246 --> 01:41:19,942
And that's all I have
to say about that.

1675
01:41:27,223 --> 01:41:29,919
Didn't you say you were waiting
for the number 7 bus?

1676
01:41:29,992 --> 01:41:32,722
There'll be another one
along shortly.

1677
01:41:36,232 --> 01:41:40,669
Now, because I had been
a football star and war hero

1678
01:41:40,736 --> 01:41:43,671
and national celebrity
and a shrimping boat captain

1679
01:41:43,739 --> 01:41:45,172
and a college graduate,

1680
01:41:45,241 --> 01:41:47,675
the city fathers
of Greenbow, Alabama,

1681
01:41:47,743 --> 01:41:50,234
decided to get together
and offered me a fine job.

1682
01:41:51,747 --> 01:41:55,274
<i>So I never went back to work
for Lieutenant Dan,</i>

1683
01:41:55,351 --> 01:41:58,286
<i>though he did take care
of my Bubba Gump money.</i>

1684
01:41:58,354 --> 01:42:01,289
<i>He got me invested
in some kind of fruit company.</i>

1685
01:42:01,357 --> 01:42:03,791
<i>So then I got a call from him</i>

1686
01:42:03,860 --> 01:42:06,420
<i>saying we don't have to worry
about money no more,</i>

1687
01:42:06,496 --> 01:42:10,899
and I said,
"That's good. One less thing."

1688
01:42:10,967 --> 01:42:12,764
~ I've got a new hope... ~

1689
01:42:12,835 --> 01:42:15,269
<i>Now Mama said
there's only so much fortune</i>

1690
01:42:15,338 --> 01:42:16,965
<i>a man really needs,</i>

1691
01:42:17,039 --> 01:42:20,440
<i>and the rest
is just for showing off.</i>

1692
01:42:20,510 --> 01:42:23,411
<i>So I gave a whole bunch of it</i>

1693
01:42:23,479 --> 01:42:26,744
<i>to the Foursquare Gospel Church...</i>

1694
01:42:26,816 --> 01:42:31,879
<i>and I gave a whole bunch to the
Bayou La Batre Fishing Hospital...</i>

1695
01:42:33,356 --> 01:42:35,790
<i>and even though Bubba was dead</i>

1696
01:42:35,858 --> 01:42:39,294
<i>and Lieutenant Dan said I was nuts,</i>

1697
01:42:39,362 --> 01:42:42,092
<i>I gave Bubba's mama Bubba's share.</i>

1698
01:42:45,468 --> 01:42:47,129
You know what?

1699
01:42:47,203 --> 01:42:51,139
<i>She didn't have to work
in nobody's kitchen no more.</i>

1700
01:42:51,207 --> 01:42:53,801
That smells wonderful.

1701
01:42:53,876 --> 01:42:56,310
<i>And 'cause I was a gozillionaire</i>

1702
01:42:56,379 --> 01:42:59,314
<i>and I liked doing it so much,</i>

1703
01:42:59,382 --> 01:43:02,818
<i>I cut that grass for free.</i>

1704
01:43:04,253 --> 01:43:07,689
<i>But at nighttime
when there was nothing to do</i>

1705
01:43:07,757 --> 01:43:10,191
<i>and the house was all empty,</i>

1706
01:43:10,259 --> 01:43:13,194
<i>I'd always think of Jenny.</i>

1707
01:44:16,759 --> 01:44:20,559
<i>And then... she was there.</i>

1708
01:44:53,328 --> 01:44:54,625
Hello, Forrest.

1709
01:44:54,696 --> 01:44:56,891
Hello, Jenny.

1710
01:45:07,743 --> 01:45:10,871
<i>Jenny came back
and stayed with me.</i>

1711
01:45:10,946 --> 01:45:15,781
<i>Maybe it was because
she had nowhere else to go,</i>

1712
01:45:15,851 --> 01:45:19,218
<i>or maybe it was because
she was so tired</i>

1713
01:45:19,288 --> 01:45:22,724
<i>'cause she went to bed
and slept and slept</i>

1714
01:45:22,791 --> 01:45:25,021
<i>like she hadn't slept in years.</i>

1715
01:45:25,093 --> 01:45:27,459
<i>It was wonderful
having her home.</i>

1716
01:45:27,529 --> 01:45:29,963
<i>Every day we'd take a walk,</i>

1717
01:45:30,032 --> 01:45:33,968
<i>and I'd jabber on
like a monkey in a tree,</i>

1718
01:45:34,036 --> 01:45:36,971
<i>and she'd listen about
Ping-Ponging and shrimping</i>

1719
01:45:37,039 --> 01:45:39,974
<i>and Mama making
a trip up to heaven.</i>

1720
01:45:40,042 --> 01:45:41,976
<i>I did all the talking.</i>

1721
01:45:42,044 --> 01:45:44,535
<i>Jenny most of the time
was real quiet.</i>

1722
01:46:24,186 --> 01:46:26,916
How could you do this?

1723
01:47:04,226 --> 01:47:08,720
<i>Sometimes I guess there
just aren't enough rocks.</i>

1724
01:47:10,232 --> 01:47:13,167
<i>I never really knew
why she came back,</i>

1725
01:47:13,235 --> 01:47:14,668
<i>but I didn't care.</i>

1726
01:47:14,736 --> 01:47:16,670
<i>It was like olden times.</i>

1727
01:47:16,738 --> 01:47:19,536
<i>We was like
peas and carrots again.</i>

1728
01:47:21,176 --> 01:47:23,610
<i>Every day,
I'd pick pretty flowers</i>

1729
01:47:23,679 --> 01:47:27,240
<i>and put them in her room for her,</i>

1730
01:47:27,316 --> 01:47:30,752
<i>and she gave me the best gift
anyone could ever get</i>

1731
01:47:30,819 --> 01:47:32,252
<i>in the wide world.</i>

1732
01:47:32,321 --> 01:47:34,846
They're made just for running.

1733
01:47:34,923 --> 01:47:36,185
<i>~ Carry me home to see my kin ~</i>

1734
01:47:38,860 --> 01:47:41,385
<i>And she even showed me
how to dance.</i>

1735
01:47:43,231 --> 01:47:45,597
<i>~ I miss ol'Bammy once again ~</i>

1736
01:47:45,667 --> 01:47:46,895
<i>~ And I think it's a sin ~</i>

1737
01:47:48,170 --> 01:47:49,831
<i>~ Sweet home Alabama... ~</i>

1738
01:47:49,905 --> 01:47:54,933
<i>Well, we was like family,
